1
00:00:00,163 --> 00:00:01,684
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,690 --> 00:00:03,010
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,553 --> 00:00:05,801
- Excuse me.
- Don't touch me!

4
00:00:05,822 --> 00:00:06,822
(Episode 5)

5
00:00:07,319 --> 00:00:08,950
I said don't touch me!

6
00:00:21,899 --> 00:00:23,417
I'm sorry.

7
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,367
Are you hurt?

8
00:00:32,331 --> 00:00:34,259
It was so dangerous, so I just reacted...

9
00:00:34,540 --> 00:00:35,634
Is something wrong?

10
00:00:36,366 --> 00:00:38,712
You shouldn't walk like that
without watching for cars.

11
00:00:40,204 --> 00:00:41,347
I'm fine.

12
00:00:43,518 --> 00:00:46,717
You're Professor Bae's assistant
from the hotel exhibition.

13
00:00:46,907 --> 00:00:48,117
You're Na Ji Ni, right?

14
00:00:50,185 --> 00:00:52,625
Thank you for today.

15
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:56,717
I'm sorry about what happened
with the competition.

16
00:00:57,909 --> 00:00:58,909
Yes.

17
00:01:00,235 --> 00:01:02,469
You should apologize
and make things right.

18
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,780
Otherwise,
you'll keep facing the consequences.

19
00:01:10,420 --> 00:01:13,434
Did you even look into it?
Do you have any proof?

20
00:01:14,442 --> 00:01:16,257
Don't jump to conclusions
when you don't know the full story.

21
00:01:16,301 --> 00:01:18,023
I heard it from the victim herself.

22
00:01:18,034 --> 00:01:20,557
I know. Do Hee told you.

23
00:01:20,590 --> 00:01:21,945
Go tell her this.

24
00:01:21,988 --> 00:01:25,708
If I ever see her again,
I won't let this slide.

25
00:01:25,735 --> 00:01:27,401
You don't seem sorry at all.

26
00:01:28,516 --> 00:01:29,571
You're hopeless.

27
00:01:29,591 --> 00:01:31,705
I'll deal with my own problems.

28
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:34,174
Just stay out of something
you know nothing about.

29
00:01:39,972 --> 00:01:42,539
This is what I get for helping her.

30
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:51,167
Are you sure you got the facts straight?

31
00:01:52,182 --> 00:01:53,819
I know what Ji Ni is like.

32
00:01:53,821 --> 00:01:55,782
She'd never do something like that.

33
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,014
Code blue, adult patient, Ward 151.

34
00:02:13,304 --> 00:02:16,316
Honey.

35
00:02:23,715 --> 00:02:25,336
Doctor!

36
00:02:26,657 --> 00:02:28,070
We've got a pulse.

37
00:02:28,092 --> 00:02:29,936
Blood pressure is coming up too.

38
00:02:30,643 --> 00:02:33,253
Keep the oxygen on
and transfer him to the ICU.

39
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,716
- Yes.
- Yes.

40
00:02:35,165 --> 00:02:38,557
Honey...

41
00:02:41,342 --> 00:02:43,918
What? Dad?

42
00:03:13,984 --> 00:03:16,091
She shoved me so hard.

43
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,075
She must've had a lot of pent-up anger.

44
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,483
She was probably hurt more than I was.

45
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:25,007
It looked dangerous, so I pulled her back.

46
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:27,328
But it turned out she was someone I knew.

47
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:30,286
Really? Someone you know?

48
00:03:30,637 --> 00:03:31,884
That's a relief.

49
00:03:32,768 --> 00:03:34,434
Actually, if I saw her,

50
00:03:34,713 --> 00:03:37,138
I was going to tell her
not to live like that.

51
00:03:38,104 --> 00:03:41,388
- Who is she?
- Do Hee's middle school bully.

52
00:03:41,809 --> 00:03:44,044
She hit her,
locked her in a storage room...

53
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,383
Do Hee still trembles because of it.

54
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,778
Even after all that,
Do Hee turned out so well.

55
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:53,037
I know, right?

56
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:56,055
But Uncle,

57
00:03:56,255 --> 00:03:58,337
there's more to her than that.

58
00:03:58,759 --> 00:04:01,238
She's a favorite student
of a professor I respect,

59
00:04:01,272 --> 00:04:03,614
and my friend says
she'd never do something like that.

60
00:04:03,689 --> 00:04:04,997
What's the truth?

61
00:04:05,683 --> 00:04:08,483
And earlier, she was crying so hard.

62
00:04:09,284 --> 00:04:10,372
I don't know...

63
00:04:11,589 --> 00:04:14,412
I keep wondering if I might be wrong.

64
00:04:14,749 --> 00:04:17,403
There's more than one side to everyone.

65
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,804
Look into it carefully.

66
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,562
Stop it.

67
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:31,583
You want to save him?

68
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,500
You really want to save that man?

69
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,510
If he's terminally ill, just let him die.

70
00:04:36,583 --> 00:04:38,409
- Seung Woo.
- What has he ever done for us?

71
00:04:38,411 --> 00:04:39,727
All he did was hurt us!

72
00:04:41,217 --> 00:04:43,835
Mom, why are you going this far?

73
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,133
I don't understand.

74
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:48,164
Please make me understand.

75
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:50,139
- Seung Woo...
- "He's still your father."

76
00:04:50,302 --> 00:04:51,964
"You studied with his money."

77
00:04:53,206 --> 00:04:54,608
Don't say that.

78
00:04:59,380 --> 00:05:00,980
If it weren't for him,

79
00:05:02,313 --> 00:05:06,080
you and I wouldn't be here,
facing each other like this.

80
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:15,440
I want to say goodbye
to my miserable twenties.

81
00:05:18,340 --> 00:05:22,459
Those messy, empty years...

82
00:05:24,773 --> 00:05:28,171
I just want to let them go.
I want to move on.

83
00:05:30,612 --> 00:05:33,477
Isn't that reason enough?

84
00:05:36,409 --> 00:05:37,861
"Say goodbye to your twenties?"

85
00:05:39,144 --> 00:05:40,411
Mom...

86
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:47,538
Your twenties were ruined
because you were deceived by a scammer.

87
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:51,984
You had two sons,
spent your life serving his parents,

88
00:05:53,284 --> 00:05:54,867
and ended up like this.

89
00:05:55,368 --> 00:05:58,549
What good are those papers?
Who even knows?

90
00:05:59,136 --> 00:06:01,411
Everyone thinks he's Na Se Ri's husband!

91
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,813
You've become a ghost, Mom. Haven't you?

92
00:06:05,815 --> 00:06:06,940
No.

93
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,177
I met him, and I had you boys.

94
00:06:10,535 --> 00:06:12,427
I was lonely, but I was happy.

95
00:06:13,636 --> 00:06:14,982
Don't talk carelessly.

96
00:06:16,407 --> 00:06:20,075
Whether I was deceived or not,
those were my twenties.

97
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:23,050
Just because your dad did that,
do you think I'm a joke too?

98
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:25,694
I may treat you like a friend,
but we're not friends.

99
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:28,885
Don't disrespect me. Watch what you say.

100
00:06:28,887 --> 00:06:31,673
When did I ever disrespect you?

101
00:06:31,675 --> 00:06:35,500
Only I get to judge that betrayal.

102
00:06:37,896 --> 00:06:39,344
Worry about your own relationship.

103
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:41,560
Don't you dare bring home the wrong woman.

104
00:06:48,462 --> 00:06:49,462
Seung Hyun...

105
00:07:00,301 --> 00:07:01,767
(Love your enemies.)

106
00:07:16,156 --> 00:07:18,573
Mom, I'm sorry.

107
00:07:19,508 --> 00:07:20,840
Please don't cry.

108
00:07:23,759 --> 00:07:27,962
Do you hate him as much as I do?
Are you as hurt as I am?

109
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:32,960
Mom.

110
00:07:36,139 --> 00:07:38,441
I hate him so much...

111
00:07:38,443 --> 00:07:41,108
I'm so hurt, Seung Hyun.

112
00:07:53,027 --> 00:07:55,334
Are you okay, Dad?

113
00:07:55,718 --> 00:07:57,033
My dear Ji Ni...

114
00:07:58,072 --> 00:07:59,406
My little girl, Ji Ni.

115
00:08:00,273 --> 00:08:03,594
Dad, you need to stay strong, okay?

116
00:08:03,662 --> 00:08:05,660
Yeah, I have to stay strong.

117
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:08,654
So I can see you paint even better...

118
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,819
and do everything you want.

119
00:08:12,307 --> 00:08:15,340
- I have to keep supporting you.
- Of course.

120
00:08:15,486 --> 00:08:17,148
You're going to do great.

121
00:08:18,590 --> 00:08:20,737
Your paintings have soul.

122
00:08:21,272 --> 00:08:23,094
You put love into every picture.

123
00:08:23,369 --> 00:08:27,831
There's comfort in the people you paint.

124
00:08:28,776 --> 00:08:32,490
That's why I loved looking at your art.

125
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:39,665
And be sure to make the animation
you've always wanted.

126
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:41,231
Okay.

127
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,880
Enough talking, Dad. Get some rest.

128
00:08:42,911 --> 00:08:45,993
I wanted you to live your life
with confidence...

129
00:08:46,974 --> 00:08:48,157
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:49,236 --> 00:08:51,540
I wanted to give you the name Cha Ji Ni...

131
00:08:53,514 --> 00:08:55,513
What's so wrong with Na Ji Ni?

132
00:08:55,853 --> 00:08:57,880
It doesn't bother me anymore.

133
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,649
A name is just a name.

134
00:09:06,849 --> 00:09:07,849
Yes.

135
00:09:13,146 --> 00:09:16,217
I came to give you this...

136
00:09:16,219 --> 00:09:17,766
It's O Reum.

137
00:09:18,189 --> 00:09:21,046
- Come in, Mai.
- Father!

138
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:22,557
Do you still remember my name?

139
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:25,440
Who? "Father?"

140
00:09:25,474 --> 00:09:28,981
Ji Ni, that's your nephew.

141
00:09:30,581 --> 00:09:32,931
His name is O Reum. Cha O Reum.

142
00:09:38,965 --> 00:09:40,838
Cha O Reum.

143
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:43,139
Does that mean you're his aunt?

144
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:44,440
That's right.

145
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,090
Ji Ni is his aunt.

146
00:09:50,083 --> 00:09:53,200
Father, try some of this.

147
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,841
Yeah, let's try some.

148
00:10:01,669 --> 00:10:02,992
Father,

149
00:10:03,276 --> 00:10:08,689
they say cancer's worst part isn't pain,
but hunger.

150
00:10:08,949 --> 00:10:13,055
- Treat it like medicine and eat up, okay?
- Yeah, thank you.

151
00:10:13,641 --> 00:10:15,240
Dad, I'll be right back.

152
00:10:21,956 --> 00:10:24,882
Mai, I said I'd give you a gift, right?

153
00:10:25,845 --> 00:10:29,597
Could you get my wallet from that drawer?

154
00:10:30,384 --> 00:10:31,634
Yes.

155
00:10:51,715 --> 00:10:54,421
- Kids, aren't the flowers pretty?
- Yes.

156
00:10:54,423 --> 00:10:57,298
- Shall we sit and look at the flowers?
- Yes.

157
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:01,421
Ji Ni! There are bubbles over there.

158
00:11:01,423 --> 00:11:03,891
- Where?
- Over there.

159
00:11:09,411 --> 00:11:11,431
What do I do...

160
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,583
Were you about to cry?

161
00:11:24,399 --> 00:11:26,128
I'm the best, right?

162
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:34,307
It's almost time to meet up.
Let's stop looking around and go.

163
00:11:37,323 --> 00:11:39,230
I was always with my dad.

164
00:11:40,275 --> 00:11:44,284
It was as if I'd been born
connected to him by an umbilical cord.

165
00:11:44,896 --> 00:11:47,392
- Congratulations!
- Thank you!

166
00:11:47,394 --> 00:11:51,017
- Congratulations, Se Ri!
- It's been so long!

167
00:11:51,019 --> 00:11:55,205
- Let's take a picture too.
- I'll take it. One, two.

168
00:11:56,568 --> 00:12:01,137
- Dad, let's go and not interrupt mom.
- Shall we?

169
00:12:27,939 --> 00:12:30,011
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

170
00:12:33,896 --> 00:12:36,024
He looks a lot like
his grandfather, right?

171
00:12:39,747 --> 00:12:40,834
Well, I'm off.

172
00:12:42,332 --> 00:12:43,335
Let's go.

173
00:12:59,311 --> 00:13:01,043
So she's doing it too?

174
00:13:03,297 --> 00:13:04,351
Do Do Hee!

175
00:13:04,752 --> 00:13:08,817
I'm here. Okay, hurry up.

176
00:13:11,895 --> 00:13:14,961
- Did you call my name?
- Yeah, I did.

177
00:13:14,964 --> 00:13:16,646
Hello again.

178
00:13:17,513 --> 00:13:19,887
Hey, Na Ji Ni!

179
00:13:19,889 --> 00:13:20,889
What?

180
00:13:21,388 --> 00:13:22,540
"What?"

181
00:13:23,893 --> 00:13:26,942
Show some respect.
You keep trying to act like my equal.

182
00:13:26,944 --> 00:13:29,241
We're the same age
and went to the same school.

183
00:13:29,243 --> 00:13:31,883
Why should I show you any respect?

184
00:13:31,885 --> 00:13:35,086
- Tell me if there's a reason.
- Seriously! Hey!

185
00:13:39,644 --> 00:13:41,516
Let go of me!

186
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,230
So we're out of school now, is that it?

187
00:13:45,232 --> 00:13:47,631
So you don't need to impress me anymore?

188
00:13:49,887 --> 00:13:52,513
You didn't make it, did you?
Here to pick up your painting?

189
00:13:53,792 --> 00:13:56,340
Your painting was good.
Why didn't it make it?

190
00:13:56,908 --> 00:14:02,244
Ji Ni, even now you don't see a reason
to stay on my good side?

191
00:14:02,489 --> 00:14:04,066
Just because I try to be nice,

192
00:14:04,068 --> 00:14:06,656
you think trash like you has nothing
to be ashamed of?

193
00:14:06,658 --> 00:14:08,042
I've got nothing to be ashamed of.

194
00:14:08,996 --> 00:14:10,387
"A child of sin?"

195
00:14:10,871 --> 00:14:13,459
It's not my sin. "A child of love?"

196
00:14:13,564 --> 00:14:14,936
That wasn't your love either.

197
00:14:14,938 --> 00:14:16,531
You and I are the same.

198
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:19,520
Did you choose your mom?
Did you know what she was like?

199
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:24,278
If you had known,
you wouldn't have chosen her either.

200
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,526
Weren't you the one
calling your own mom a bitch?

201
00:14:26,528 --> 00:14:27,762
You little...

202
00:14:27,764 --> 00:14:29,292
Touch me again and see what happens.

203
00:14:30,309 --> 00:14:34,242
I'll make you pay
for every tear you made my dad shed.

204
00:14:34,244 --> 00:14:37,424
Look at you acting tough.

205
00:14:41,656 --> 00:14:45,093
- Let's not do this...
- Don't touch me!

206
00:14:45,452 --> 00:14:47,058
I'm sorry.

207
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:49,699
I'm sorry, Ji Ni. I was wrong.

208
00:14:50,547 --> 00:14:53,782
- Please, don't do this.
- Get up.

209
00:14:53,898 --> 00:14:55,534
It hurts so much.

210
00:14:58,790 --> 00:15:01,325
- Do Hee!
- Ji Hu!

211
00:15:01,514 --> 00:15:02,853
Are you okay?

212
00:15:08,331 --> 00:15:10,130
You're terrifying.

213
00:15:10,749 --> 00:15:12,588
Everyone said
you'd never do something like that,

214
00:15:12,590 --> 00:15:14,355
so I wondered if I was wrong.

215
00:15:14,627 --> 00:15:16,135
But now I'm sure.

216
00:15:16,307 --> 00:15:18,699
How did you hide this side of yourself?

217
00:15:18,701 --> 00:15:20,811
I feel sorry for Professor Bae
for trusting you.

218
00:15:24,164 --> 00:15:26,052
No, don't.

219
00:15:26,204 --> 00:15:28,126
Don't tell the professor.

220
00:15:28,351 --> 00:15:30,936
Ji Ni's still talented
and good at drawing.

221
00:15:30,939 --> 00:15:33,128
After everything she did to you,
you can still say that?

222
00:15:34,409 --> 00:15:35,638
You're too kind.

223
00:15:50,307 --> 00:15:51,326
(Na Se Ri's Cello Recital)

224
00:15:51,339 --> 00:15:53,338
We'll begin the final rehearsal.

225
00:16:20,948 --> 00:16:22,033
Honey...

226
00:16:32,622 --> 00:16:36,959
Mom, this piece makes me sad.

227
00:16:36,961 --> 00:16:38,675
Do you feel that way too?

228
00:16:38,677 --> 00:16:42,329
"Sad?" You little thing.

229
00:16:42,331 --> 00:16:46,157
Maybe it's because I listened to it often
when I was pregnant with you.

230
00:16:46,159 --> 00:16:50,798
Then when I was in your belly,
were you sad too?

231
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:56,641
"Sad?" I couldn't have been happier.

232
00:16:56,769 --> 00:16:58,837
Let's not listen to this piece anymore.

233
00:16:58,899 --> 00:17:02,443
I don't want my daughter to feel sad.

234
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:13,441
Get out right now!
How dare you disrespect our family?

235
00:17:13,443 --> 00:17:16,008
Please let me divorce her. It's my life.

236
00:17:16,010 --> 00:17:18,211
You have no reason to interfere this much.

237
00:17:19,581 --> 00:17:22,084
Please give me just one chance, Father.

238
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:24,195
I promise I'll do better.

239
00:17:29,798 --> 00:17:32,286
- Mother!
- You shameless woman!

240
00:17:32,288 --> 00:17:34,570
Don't ever show your face here again!

241
00:17:38,026 --> 00:17:40,602
- Thank you.
- Congratulations, Se Ri!

242
00:17:40,604 --> 00:17:42,485
- It's so beautiful.
- It's been so long!

243
00:17:42,487 --> 00:17:46,828
- Let's take a picture too.
- I'll take it. One, two.

244
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:50,677
- Dad, let's go and not interrupt mom.
- Shall we?

245
00:17:50,679 --> 00:17:52,229
You're so beautiful.

246
00:17:52,231 --> 00:17:53,384
Let's go.

247
00:18:23,025 --> 00:18:26,107
- Have you been waiting long?
- No.

248
00:18:28,335 --> 00:18:30,490
After watching your rehearsal,

249
00:18:30,492 --> 00:18:32,134
I really enjoy waiting here alone.

250
00:18:32,380 --> 00:18:34,259
It's like the performance is just for me.

251
00:18:34,261 --> 00:18:36,617
I'm always grateful.

252
00:18:37,109 --> 00:18:38,742
I'll have the same, please.

253
00:18:39,736 --> 00:18:43,418
It's been 25 years already.
I realized it on my way here.

254
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:45,288
Why did you suddenly think of that?

255
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:52,557
- I told you my husband was sick, right?
- Yes. How is he doing?

256
00:18:53,481 --> 00:18:55,465
He probably won't come tomorrow either.

257
00:18:59,251 --> 00:19:01,233
Since he got sick,

258
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:05,811
whenever I meet someone, I wonder,
"How long have we known each other?"

259
00:19:05,997 --> 00:19:07,847
It's become a habit.

260
00:19:09,421 --> 00:19:10,722
I don't know why.

261
00:19:11,529 --> 00:19:13,547
I think I understand.

262
00:19:13,862 --> 00:19:16,557
Is it serious enough
to make you think this way?

263
00:19:16,559 --> 00:19:17,915
Earlier today,

264
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,515
they told me to prepare for the worst.

265
00:19:25,808 --> 00:19:27,084
Sa Bin.

266
00:19:27,892 --> 00:19:28,967
I...

267
00:19:32,751 --> 00:19:36,178
I've never done right by him.

268
00:19:37,635 --> 00:19:41,517
My performances, my goals...

269
00:19:42,753 --> 00:19:44,709
That's all I ever talked about.

270
00:19:47,944 --> 00:19:49,380
Even now, I'm still the same.

271
00:19:49,382 --> 00:19:55,027
Anyone else would've canceled everything
and stayed by her husband's side.

272
00:19:55,030 --> 00:19:57,750
Are you uncomfortable
being by your husband's side?

273
00:20:00,655 --> 00:20:03,606
I hate hearing him say
he lived his life all wrong.

274
00:20:04,696 --> 00:20:06,403
It feels like he's denying...

275
00:20:06,446 --> 00:20:08,530
and regretting the life we had together.

276
00:20:08,738 --> 00:20:09,945
I'm sure that's not true.

277
00:20:09,946 --> 00:20:12,196
Being sick makes people vulnerable.

278
00:20:13,571 --> 00:20:15,496
I thought that if he got sick,

279
00:20:15,613 --> 00:20:17,843
he'd regret what he did to me.

280
00:20:19,289 --> 00:20:20,616
But he...

281
00:20:21,738 --> 00:20:23,028
regrets me.

282
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:26,783
I feel like he regrets ever meeting me.

283
00:20:27,488 --> 00:20:28,696
No way.

284
00:20:29,405 --> 00:20:30,852
Let's stop talking about this.

285
00:20:31,155 --> 00:20:32,770
Sorry, I got too serious.

286
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:42,264
Thank you. I couldn't tell anyone this.

287
00:20:43,196 --> 00:20:45,177
What am I going to do
when you get married?

288
00:20:45,321 --> 00:20:46,780
Whether I get married or not,

289
00:20:46,821 --> 00:20:49,946
I'm still your number one fan.
Call me anytime.

290
00:20:52,655 --> 00:20:55,316
You're like an energy bar to me.

291
00:20:55,376 --> 00:20:57,136
Thank you for giving me strength.

292
00:20:58,030 --> 00:21:00,071
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

293
00:21:15,655 --> 00:21:17,030
Honey.

294
00:21:18,238 --> 00:21:19,660
Min Ki.

295
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:22,530
Cha Min Ki.

296
00:21:27,821 --> 00:21:31,248
How can we say goodbye like this?

297
00:21:36,792 --> 00:21:40,401
You can't die. Don't die.

298
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:45,309
We said we'd live a long life...

299
00:21:45,738 --> 00:21:48,670
because we've taken so much criticism.

300
00:21:52,655 --> 00:21:53,863
Se Ri.

301
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:57,446
Honey, are you okay?

302
00:21:58,266 --> 00:21:59,679
Did I wake you?

303
00:21:59,738 --> 00:22:02,030
Why are you crying?

304
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,453
Because I'm upset.

305
00:22:05,988 --> 00:22:08,253
What's this?

306
00:22:12,196 --> 00:22:14,183
Should I die with you?

307
00:22:15,636 --> 00:22:17,127
That's so like you.

308
00:22:17,664 --> 00:22:20,781
You always do the unexpected.

309
00:22:23,530 --> 00:22:24,738
Honey.

310
00:22:26,571 --> 00:22:28,131
Let's die together.

311
00:22:32,905 --> 00:22:34,787
If you leave without even
taking care of the paperwork,

312
00:22:34,863 --> 00:22:38,612
what are Ji Ni and I supposed to do?

313
00:22:38,613 --> 00:22:40,379
You jerk!

314
00:22:48,988 --> 00:22:50,863
Don't die.

315
00:22:52,363 --> 00:22:53,820
(Haemyeong University Hospital)

316
00:22:53,821 --> 00:22:54,905
Seung Woo.

317
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:57,155
I'll accept your apology.

318
00:22:57,780 --> 00:22:59,321
I'll take it,

319
00:22:59,871 --> 00:23:01,079
so you can go in peace.

320
00:23:01,988 --> 00:23:04,112
And stop bothering Seung Hyun
and his wife.

321
00:23:04,113 --> 00:23:05,912
Seung Woo, that's not what this is about.

322
00:23:07,655 --> 00:23:08,863
Then what is it?

323
00:23:09,473 --> 00:23:11,363
He lived however he wanted,

324
00:23:11,488 --> 00:23:13,232
and now he apologizes,

325
00:23:13,613 --> 00:23:15,363
just so he can die in peace.

326
00:23:15,446 --> 00:23:17,863
In his entire life,

327
00:23:17,905 --> 00:23:20,654
did he ever once think of us?
If he did, say it.

328
00:23:20,655 --> 00:23:21,863
You're right. I'm sorry.

329
00:23:22,168 --> 00:23:23,531
That's all I have to say.

330
00:23:24,512 --> 00:23:25,785
Fine.

331
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:27,696
Go in peace.

332
00:23:27,946 --> 00:23:30,530
I never forgot you. I mean it.

333
00:23:31,738 --> 00:23:33,521
I can't listen to this.

334
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,550
I was never your son.

335
00:23:41,696 --> 00:23:43,790
What I remember about you...

336
00:23:44,905 --> 00:23:46,920
is that when I called you,
you pretended not to hear.

337
00:23:48,363 --> 00:23:51,952
Even when I tried so hard
to reach your level,

338
00:23:53,530 --> 00:23:54,946
you acted like you didn't see me.

339
00:23:55,961 --> 00:23:57,088
Isn't that right?

340
00:23:57,946 --> 00:24:00,238
To you, Ji Ni was your only child.

341
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:02,029
No, that's not true!

342
00:24:02,030 --> 00:24:05,030
Even animals don't act like that.

343
00:24:06,030 --> 00:24:08,862
I can't listen to this anymore.

344
00:24:08,863 --> 00:24:10,780
Your father said he'd do everything.

345
00:24:10,821 --> 00:24:13,487
It was your mother who drove him away.

346
00:24:13,488 --> 00:24:16,696
If she'd just agreed to the divorce,
why would he have cut ties with his kids?

347
00:24:16,738 --> 00:24:18,963
Do you know how much he thought of you?

348
00:24:18,988 --> 00:24:21,030
- Get out.
- Why are you just taking this?

349
00:24:21,071 --> 00:24:22,571
You loved them.

350
00:24:22,655 --> 00:24:24,753
You missed them so much.

351
00:24:25,376 --> 00:24:26,473
Don't go.

352
00:24:44,155 --> 00:24:46,559
What do you even know?

353
00:24:48,238 --> 00:24:50,337
My dad disappeared overnight.

354
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:52,405
And at school, they said,

355
00:24:53,511 --> 00:24:56,132
"Your dad ran off with another woman."

356
00:24:56,321 --> 00:24:57,530
They called me...

357
00:24:58,196 --> 00:25:00,015
"a bastard with no father."

358
00:25:00,609 --> 00:25:02,044
That's what they said.

359
00:25:04,043 --> 00:25:05,043
(Divorce Papers)

360
00:25:13,238 --> 00:25:16,530
Dad, I want to live with you.

361
00:25:17,113 --> 00:25:19,946
Don't go. Take me with you.

362
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:21,530
Dad...

363
00:25:23,488 --> 00:25:25,571
Seung Woo, don't.

364
00:25:28,780 --> 00:25:31,322
I'm going abroad for work.

365
00:25:32,234 --> 00:25:34,067
Be good and listen to Grandpa and Mom.

366
00:25:34,238 --> 00:25:35,868
You want to be a soccer player, right?

367
00:25:35,997 --> 00:25:37,695
I'll come back with a present for you.

368
00:25:42,446 --> 00:25:44,571
- Dad!
- Seung Woo!

369
00:25:44,946 --> 00:25:48,071
- I said you can't go!
- Dad!

370
00:25:54,905 --> 00:25:56,071
Let me go!

371
00:25:57,155 --> 00:25:58,363
Dad.

372
00:26:02,113 --> 00:26:03,821
Dad.

373
00:26:03,946 --> 00:26:05,113
Drive away now.

374
00:26:05,238 --> 00:26:06,446
Dad!

375
00:26:10,030 --> 00:26:11,378
Dad.

376
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:14,238
Dad.

377
00:26:17,363 --> 00:26:18,571
Dad!

378
00:26:28,821 --> 00:26:30,030
What was that?

379
00:26:31,030 --> 00:26:32,238
A cat.

380
00:26:32,738 --> 00:26:34,946
It came out of nowhere.

381
00:27:12,738 --> 00:27:13,988
It's over now.

382
00:27:14,071 --> 00:27:15,280
I'm sorry.

383
00:27:15,946 --> 00:27:17,657
I'm truly sorry.

384
00:27:18,655 --> 00:27:19,863
I told you, that's enough!

385
00:27:19,946 --> 00:27:21,639
Please stop it.

386
00:27:22,196 --> 00:27:23,342
Hey.

387
00:27:24,196 --> 00:27:25,946
Seung Woo, I was wrong.

388
00:27:26,821 --> 00:27:29,363
He said that's enough. Stop.

389
00:27:29,613 --> 00:27:32,315
If you beg him like this,
what does that make Ji Ni and me?

390
00:27:32,488 --> 00:27:34,613
Get up.

391
00:27:40,821 --> 00:27:43,916
Who are you to reject his apology?

392
00:27:43,988 --> 00:27:45,655
Just accept it!

393
00:27:49,568 --> 00:27:53,058
You, of all people,
should stay out of our family matters.

394
00:27:53,530 --> 00:27:54,738
Yeong Ju!

395
00:28:24,165 --> 00:28:27,405
(Family Register)

396
00:28:27,530 --> 00:28:29,445
He's my husband and my daughter's father!

397
00:28:29,446 --> 00:28:32,070
If she hadn't been born,
Dad would've come back home.

398
00:28:32,071 --> 00:28:35,362
Is this love?
The love you said you'd die for?

399
00:28:35,363 --> 00:28:36,654
I don't believe the bullying rumors.

400
00:28:36,655 --> 00:28:38,405
No one who paints like this would do that.

401
00:28:38,530 --> 00:28:41,238
An artist can't be so different
from their work.

402
00:28:42,196 --> 00:28:44,071
So that's your precious little paper.

403
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:46,446
It's not some diploma to be proud of.

404
00:28:46,530 --> 00:28:49,503
Go ahead and make a big deal of it.
I'm not scared!

405
00:28:50,309 --> 00:28:52,309
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
